AB  - Efficient yard management is essential for container terminal operations. This paper presents an IoT-enabled digital twin (DT) architecture for yard management in semi-automated container terminals. The architecture integrates RFID sensors, GPS-equipped RTG cranes, and an edge computing layer to maintain a real-time digital representation of yard state. A data integration ontology aligns container, stack, and crane states across heterogeneous data sources (operational state layer L2). A rule-based decision support module (L3) uses the DT state to generate stack rearrangement plans that minimize crane moves. A hardware-in-the-loop validation was conducted at a medium-sized terminal (approximately 0.9 million TEU/year), demonstrating 12% improvement in yard crane utilization. The proposed lightweight DT components (RFID + edge compute + open-source stack) make it applicable to resource-constrained small and mid-size container ports.
