AB  - Digital twin (DT) technology is increasingly adopted in maritime logistics and container terminal operations. This systematic literature review examines 87 publications from 2015 to 2023 addressing DT applications in seaports and terminal facilities. We analyze the maturity spectrum from data visibility (L1) to closed-loop autonomy (L5), identifying significant research gaps at L4 and L5 for container terminals. The review covers five operational domains: berth allocation, yard management, quay crane scheduling, AGV dispatching, and gate operations. We find that most existing research operates at L1-L3, with limited evidence of V&V frameworks and closed-loop autonomy. A research agenda for DT-driven port intelligence is proposed, including lightweight DT architectures for resource-constrained mid-size ports in developing countries. Geographic analysis reveals dominance of European and East Asian research, with Southeast Asian ports significantly underrepresented.
