AB  - Berth allocation at container ports is a critical operational bottleneck affecting port throughput and vessel waiting time. This study develops a digital shadow for a major seaport, continuously updated with AIS vessel data and terminal operating system (TOS) logs. A mixed-integer linear programming (MILP) model is solved using Benders decomposition over a rolling time horizon, leveraging real-time port state from the digital shadow.
