AB  - Container terminal operations involve complex interactions among berths, quay cranes, yard equipment, and gate systems. This paper presents a comprehensive digital twin (DT) framework covering the full container terminal workflow from ship-to-shore to gate-out. The DT integrates IoT sensors across all operational zones: AIS vessel tracking at berths, crane position encoders, RFID in the yard, and license plate readers at gates. A data integration ontology enables interoperability across the five operational domains. Decision support modules (L3) optimize crane-to-truck handover and truck appointment scheduling simultaneously. The system is demonstrated at a medium-sized greenfield container terminal in the Middle East (approximately 1.5 million TEU/year). A partial closed-loop feedback mechanism is realized for gate operations, with the crane and berth modules remaining at L3. The paper discusses the resource requirements and suggests a phased implementation roadmap for brownfield terminals.
