AB  - The construction industry is undergoing digitalization through Building Information Modeling (BIM) and IoT integration. This paper presents a digital twin framework for construction project lifecycle management. The BIM model serves as the spatial data backbone, while IoT sensors on construction equipment and material inventory provide real-time updates. A machine learning module predicts construction schedule delays based on weather data and equipment utilization. The framework is demonstrated on a large-scale civil construction project. BIM-integrated digital twins enable collaboration between architects, engineers, and contractors through a shared data environment. Applications to port infrastructure construction (quay walls, berths) are mentioned as future extensions, but the primary focus is civil construction management.
