AB  - Predictive maintenance of port crane systems is critical for minimizing unplanned downtime in container terminals. This paper presents a digital twin-based predictive maintenance system for quay cranes and RTG cranes at container terminals. The system integrates vibration sensors, motor current analyzers, and visual inspection cameras into an edge computing architecture. A digital twin of each crane maintains a real-time mechanical state model (L2) that feeds a machine learning predictive maintenance module (L3). The lightweight IoT architecture uses low-cost MEMS sensors and Raspberry Pi edge nodes, making it deployable at mid-size container terminals with limited capital budgets. Validation at a brownfield container terminal handling 0.8 million TEU/year in Southeast Asia demonstrates a 62% reduction in unplanned crane failures. The framework is designed as a modular add-on for legacy TOS environments.
