TI  - Feasibility assessment of digital twin adoption for Cat Lai container terminal, Vietnam: a maturity-level framework
PY  - 2024
T2  - Journal of Marine Science and Engineering
VL  - 12
IS  - 4
SP  - 612
DO  - 10.3390/jmse12040612
AB  - Cat Lai Container Terminal, the largest container terminal in Vietnam with approximately 5 million TEU annual throughput, is exploring digital twin (DT) adoption as part of the national port digitalization strategy. This paper assesses the feasibility of DT adoption at Cat Lai using a maturity-level framework (L1-L5). Current operational state is evaluated as L1 (basic IoT monitoring) based on existing RFID and CCTV infrastructure. An implementation roadmap to L2-L3 is proposed over 3 years, covering data integration with TOS, ontology development for port operations, and decision support for berth and yard scheduling. Resource requirements are estimated at medium intensity (IoT expansion + cloud integration + 5 data engineers). The paper discusses brownfield integration challenges with legacy Navis TOS and provides cost-benefit analysis for each maturity level transition. The framework is recommended for adoption by other mid-size ports in Southeast Asia, including Da Nang, Quy Nhon, and Hai Phong terminals.
