TI  - Data integration ontology for operational state modeling in Hai Phong container port: a digital twin layer-2 approach
PY  - 2025
T2  - Computers in Industry
VL  - 165
SP  - 104190
DO  - 10.1016/j.compind.2025.104190
AB  - Hai Phong Port Complex is the primary container gateway of Northern Vietnam, handling approximately 2.8 million TEU/year across multiple terminals. This paper presents a data integration ontology for operational state modeling at Hai Phong container terminals, implementing the digital twin maturity level L2 (operational state). The ontology harmonizes data from three heterogeneous terminal operating systems (Navis N4, CTOS, in-house TOS) and integrates AIS vessel data, RFID yard data, and truck GPS tracking. An OWL 2 ontology with 145 classes and 89 object properties represents the complete container lifecycle from vessel arrival to gate-out. A SPARQL query interface enables real-time state queries for berth planning and yard management decision support. Evaluation on 90 days of operational data demonstrates 98.7% ontology coverage of observed events. The paper discusses scalability to Da Nang and Cai Mep terminals with brownfield TOS environments. This work is positioned as the data foundation for future L3 optimization and L4 simulation capabilities.
