TI  - Simulation-based digital twin for small container terminal scheduling
PY  - 2023
T2  - Journal of Shipping and Trade
AB  - This paper presents a simulation-based digital twin approach for scheduling operations at small container terminals with fewer than 500,000 TEU annual throughput. The simulation model integrates real-time data from a simplified IoT sensor network to maintain a digital representation of terminal state. A greedy heuristic provides scheduling recommendations for berth and crane operations. The framework is designed for minimal computational resources and uses entirely open-source tools (SimPy, Python, InfluxDB). Case study at a small regional port in Southeast Asia demonstrates feasibility.
